% Ad-hoc baseline (A0): refund service described in prose without contract sections.

Build a refund payment service that:

- Rejects zero or negative refund amounts when an amount is provided.
- Never refunds more than the original charge.
- Does not call the payment provider when validation already failed.
- Reuses the same idempotency key when retrying with the same refund id.
- Writes an audit log when the provider confirms success.
- Never logs or returns provider credentials.

Also handle disputes outside this module and do not store card data here.
